                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">You started off so well - the mobs are broken.  But instead of trying to fix the mobs, you suggested killing charm and making it something entirely different.
<br />

<br />
My proposal for a fix has been the following:
<br />
1.  Do not scale mob power in relation to player power.  If it takes a level 50 mob 20 seconds to kill a player at level 50, then it should take a level 70 mob 20 seconds to kill a player at level 70.
<br />
2.  Old zones were a lot of fun because adds were a common problem.  You would need mez, off-tanking, pet-tanking, pacify to try and control the situation.  Because of the scaling of mob power, pacify pulling has become the ONLY method for dealing with "challenging" content.  Scale back mob power and increase multi-mob encounters and you will have the same challenging content that people enjoyed years ago without having to deal with uber mob that kills enchanters in 6 seconds flat.
<br />
3.  Add new strategies to mob AI so that players have to use varying tactics to beat them.  Even with the uber mobs of today, the game can get pretty boring when you just apply the same tactic ad nauseum.
<br />

<br />
If you do this, charm is no longer unbalanced because the mobs that the enchanter controls are not unbalanced.  If Sony did this, I think they would be amazed at how many player complaints would disappear.  I think that much of the class frustration these days is that players have become weaker and weaker.  But most players have chosen to compare themselves against other players as opposed to the mobs which are out of whack.  Make the player feel powerful again, and Sony would have a much happier playerbase.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
