                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Excellent post Sphynix.
<br />

<br />
I agree with the following proviso:
<br />

<br />
IF SoE is unwilling to adjust max hit of charmed pets up to a reasonable range (e.g. 65 to 80 pct of normal), then they should simply terminate charm where it is.
<br />

<br />
The illusion idea is interesting.  Who knows, maybe enchanters could take on the appearance and some of the abilities of mobs for a short time?  Unfortunately, I don't hold out hope for such a change, as it would probably require a lot of coding and testing - and therefore would take months to implement.
<br />

<br />
The longer the current situation persists, the more enchanters will leave the game.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><span style="color: darkblue"> 
<br />
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=831098" target="_blank" class="postlink">Visionary Nokei Orhaste</a></span>
<br />
Coercer for <span style="color: blue"><a href="http://www.houseofaegis.com" target="_blank" class="postlink">House of Aegis</a></span>
<br />
Luclin
